3. Hardcoded Sleep - the user uses time.sleep(), which could make the tests flaky and slow
3 - Proposed Fix: Add page.wait_for_selector() provided by Playwright which will wait until this selector is visible and you can interact with it

4. Missing context management - The user is not using "With" statement for a proper tearup and cleanup of the code after it ran.
4. Proposed Fix: Add with: statement as seen below

5. Missing documentation - Without proper documentation of what we're doing and funtions, the next developer will have problems understanding the code.
